To fix the code quality issue of having a console.log statement in production code, you should remove or comment out the console.log statement in the `route.ts` file. 

Here is an example of how you can do this:

Before:
```typescript
console.log('Processing task...');
// Your existing code here
```

After:
```typescript
// console.log('Processing task...');
// Your existing code here
```

By commenting out or removing the console.log statement, you can ensure that it does not interfere with the production code and improve the overall quality of the codebase.